88.1	Tadao_Ando	Tadao Ando	Tadao Ando And≈ç Tadao, born September 13, 1941, in Minato-ku, Osaka, Japan and raised in Asahi-ku in the city) is a Japanese architect whose approach to architecture was categorized by Francesco Dal Co as critical regionalism. Ando has led a storied life, working as a truck driver and boxer prior to settling on the profession of architecture, despite never having taken formal training in the field. He visited buildings designed by renowned architects like Le Corbusier, Ludwig Mies Van der Rohe, Frank Lloyd Wright and Louis Kahn before returning to Osaka in 1968 and established his own design studio, Tadao Ando Architect and Associates.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/Tadao_Ando_2004.jpg/220px-Tadao_Ando_2004.jpg
